title: Specified transaction scope
explanation: The text explicitly amends the definition of 'Specified Transaction' in Section 14 by adding 'margin loan' and making other modifications, indicating a non-standard scope.

title: Cross default applicable parties
explanation: The text states that the 'Cross-Default' provisions of Section 5(a)(vi) will apply, but does not specify only one party. In ISDA Schedules, if not limited, this typically means both parties (Party A and Party B).

title: Specified indebtness includes borrowed_money
explanation: The text does not mention whether borrowed money is included in Specified Indebtedness; it only refers to the definition in Section 14 and an exclusion for deposits.

title: Specified indebtness excludes deposits
explanation: The text explicitly states that Specified Indebtedness shall exclude, in relation to Party A, any deposits received in the ordinary course of business.

title: Party for calculation agent
value: Party A (unless an Event of Default occurs and is continuing in respect of Party A, in which case Party B or an Independent Dealer selected by Party B)
explanation: The text states that the Calculation Agent will be Party A, except if an Event of Default occurs and is continuing in respect of Party A, in which case it will be Party B or an Independent Dealer selected by Party B.
